# .nvmrc — pins the Node.js version for this repository.
#
# WHAT THIS FILE IS FOR
#   nvm (and compatible tools such as fnm and Volta) read this file and select
#   the version named below whenever you run `nvm use` inside this project. This
#   keeps every contributor, CI (actions/setup-node), and the editor on one Node
#   runtime, so Hardhat, the deploy/test scripts, and the frontend build all run
#   against the same interpreter — matching the `engines.node` floor (>=22) in
#   package.json.
#
# WHEN TO CHANGE THE VERSION
#   - Only when the project intentionally adopts a new Node release (a
#     dependency requires it, or to pick up an LTS/security update).
#   - Install the new version with nvm first, then update the line below:
#         nvm ls-remote --lts       # see available LTS versions
#         nvm install <version>     # install it
#         (edit the version line below to match)
#   - Keep it in sync with CI (actions/setup-node `node-version`) and the
#     `engines.node` range in package.json, so local, CI, and editor all agree.
#   - After switching, reinstall dependencies in the new runtime:
#         npm ci
#
# NOTE: nvm (>=0.40) strips these comment lines. The single non-comment line
# below is the active version — keep exactly one version line.
22.22.3
